    "title": "Building your project with embedded shader sources"
  },
  "primaryContentSections": [
    {
      "content": [
        {
          "anchor": "Overview",
          "level": 2,
          "text": "Overview",
          "type": "heading"
        },
        {
          "inlineContent": [
            {
              "text": "To debug your shaders in Xcode, configure your build to include shader source code by changing your project’s build settings.",
              "type": "text"
            },
            {
              "text": " ",
              "type": "text"
            },
            {
              "text": "Select your project in the Project navigator, click the Build Settings tab, and search for the Produce Debugging Information setting in the Metal Compiler Build Options section.",
              "type": "text"
            },
            {
              "text": " ",
              "type": "text"
            },
            {
              "text": "Then, change the setting’s Debug entry to “Yes, include source code.”",
              "type": "text"
            }
          ],
          "type": "paragraph"
        },
        {
          "inlineContent": [
            {
              "identifier": "gputools-metal-debugger-se-include-sources.png",
              "type": "image"
            }
          ],
          "type": "paragraph"
        },
        {
          "inlineContent": [
            {
              "text": "Alternatively, you can debug the shaders that you compile for release by generating a separate symbol file for each Metal library in your project.",
              "type": "text"
            },
            {
              "text": " ",
              "type": "text"
            },
            {
              "text": "For more information on using this approach, see ",
              "type": "text"
            },
            {
              "identifier": "doc://com.apple.documentation/documentation/Metal/generating-and-loading-a-metal-library-symbol-file",
              "isActive": true,
              "type": "reference"
            },
            {
              "text": ".",
              "type": "text"
            }
          ],
          "type": "paragraph"
        },
        {
          "content": [
            {
              "inlineContent": [
                {
                  "text": "To ensure you don’t include debugging information in apps you ship to customers, be sure to reset the Produce Debugging Information for Release option to No when you finish debugging.",
                  "type": "text"
                }
              ],
              "type": "paragraph"
            }
          ],
          "name": "Important",
          "style": "important",
          "type": "aside"
        }
      ],
      "kind": "content"
    }
  ],
